The White House has announced that Tina Tchen has been promoted to Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the First Lady. Tchen previously served as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of the Office of Public Engagement, as well as Executive Director of the White House Council on Women and Girls. She will continue to serve as Executive Director of the Council in her new position. Mrs. Obama expressed her excitement in welcoming Tchen to her team and praised her work in ensuring that communities across the country have a voice and presence at the White House. Tchen's experience leading the Office of Public Engagement and reaching out to people across the country makes her uniquely qualified for the role. Valerie Jarrett, Chair of the White House Council on Women and Girls, also praised Tchen for her advocacy for women and families. Prior to her work in the White House, Tchen was a partner at a law firm in Chicago.